  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is typically defined under the law as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements usually include:\n\n1. Concealing the origin of illegally obtained funds\n2. Transferring money through multiple accounts or transactions\n3. Creating the appearance that funds are from a legal source\n4. Attempting to disguise the true ownership or nature of funds\n\nLegal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but generally involve three stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (conducting complex transactions to obscure origin)\n- Integration (reintroducing funds as seemingly legitimate)\n\nThe specific details and penalties depend on each country's specific legal statutes.",
